      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">13.501</ph> Special documentation
requirements.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d774e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d795e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> Sole source (including brand name)
acquisitions.</p>
               <ol id="d774e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d795e16" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Acquisitions conducted under simplified
acquisition procedures are exempt from the requirements in <xref href="FAR-i1120119.dita#i1120119"
                              base="i1120119"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  6</xref>. However, contracting
officers must-</p>
                     <ol id="d774e36" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d795e25" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Conduct sole source acquisitions,
as defined in <xref href="FAR-i1125359.dita#i1125359"
                                    base="i1125359"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>,
(including brand name) under this subpart only if the need to do
so is justified in writing and approved at the levels specified
in paragraph (a)(2) of this section;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d795e33" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Prepare
sole source (including brand name) justifications using the format
at <xref href="FAR-i1119771.dita#i1119771"
                                    base="i1119771"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.303-2</xref>, modified to reflect
that the procedures in FAR <xref href="FAR-i1111258.dita#i1111258"
                                    base="i1111258"
                                    outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">subpart  13.5</xref> were
used in accordance with <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.1901</xref> or the
authority of <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.1903</xref>;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d795e50" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph> Make publicly
available the justifications (excluding brand name) required by <xref href="FAR-i1119843.dita#i1119843"
                                    base="i1119843"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.305</xref>(a) within 14 days
after contract award or in the case of unusual and compelling urgency
within 30 days after contract award, in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1119843.dita#i1119843"
                                    base="i1119843"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.305</xref> procedures at paragraphs
(b), (d), (e), and (f); and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d795e61" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iv)</ph> Make publicly
available brand name justifications with the solicitation, in accordance
with <xref href="FAR-i1121037.dita#i1121037"
                                    base="i1121037"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">5.102</xref>(a)(6).</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d795e69" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Justifications
and approvals are required under this subpart for sole-source (including
brand-name) acquisitions or portions of an acquisition requiring
a brand-name. If the justification is to cover only the portion
of the acquisition which is brand-name, then it should so state;
the approval level requirements will then only apply to that portion.</p>
                     <ol id="d774e108" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d795e75" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> For
a proposed contract exceeding <ph rev="FAC 2020-06 June 5, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-007?>the
simplified acquisition threshold,<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 13.501 by removing from paragraph (a)(2)(i) “$150,000” and adding “the simplified acquisition threshold” in its place.?></ph> but not exceeding $700,000,
the contracting officer’s certification that the justification is
accurate and complete to the best of the contracting officer’s knowledge
and belief will serve as approval, unless a higher approval level
is established in accordance with agency procedures.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d795e85" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> For a proposed
contract exceeding $700,000, but not exceeding $13.5 million, the
advocate for competition for the procuring activity, designated
pursuant to <xref href="FAR-i1119317.dita#i1119317"
                                    base="i1119317"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.501</xref>; or an official
described in <xref href="FAR-i1119818.dita#i1119818"
                                    base="i1119818"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.304</xref>(a)(3) or (a)(4)
must approve the justification and approval. This authority is not
delegable.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d795e96" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph> For a
proposed contract exceeding $13.5 million but not exceeding $68
million or, for DoD, NASA, and the Coast Guard, not exceeding $93
million, the head of the procuring activity or the official described
in <xref href="FAR-i1119818.dita#i1119818"
                                    base="i1119818"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.304</xref>(a)(3) or (a)(4)
must approve the justification and approval. This authority is not
delegable.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d795e104" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iv)</ph> For a proposed
contract exceeding $68 million or, for DoD, NASA, and the Coast
Guard, $93 million, the official described in <xref href="FAR-i1119818.dita#i1119818"
                                    base="i1119818"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.304</xref>(a)(4) must approve
the justification and approval. This authority is not delegable
except as provided in <xref href="FAR-i1119818.dita#i1119818"
                                    base="i1119818"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">6.304</xref>(a)(4).</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d795e115" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Contract
file documentation.</i> The contract file must include-</p>
               <ol id="d774e176" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d795e123" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> A
brief written description of the procedures used in awarding the
contract, including the fact that the procedures in FAR <xref href="FAR-i1111258.dita#i1111258"
                              base="i1111258"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  13.5</xref> were
used;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d795e131" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> The number
of offers received;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d795e136" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> An explanation,
tailored to the size and complexity of the acquisition, of the basis
for the contract award decision; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d795e141" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph> Any justification
approved under paragraph (a) of this section.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
